1
00:01:45,397 --> 00:01:47,858
Scared the living crap out of me.

2
00:01:47,858 --> 00:01:49,860
Meryl Streep she wasn't.

3
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:51,695
Who's Meryl Streep?

4
00:01:51,695 --> 00:01:54,823
Zoe, she's like Katie Holmes
to our parents.

5
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:57,534
So, what's next, ladies?

6
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:59,411
-I have to go home.
-No.

7
00:01:59,411 --> 00:02:03,415
I can't have another fight with
my parents. They think I'm in bed.

8
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,710
Were you kids in bed early?

9
00:02:06,710 --> 00:02:10,172
-I stayed up till 10.
-After 9, Rhett was asleep.

10
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:12,174
-Who's driving them?
-I will.

11
00:02:12,174 --> 00:02:16,178
Nicki's selling coffee at school,
I'm helping her.

12
00:02:17,179 --> 00:02:18,472
It sucks.

13
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:22,476
Do not say "sucks," say "disappoints."

14
00:02:25,187 --> 00:02:27,898
I don't need a lunch.
I'll go with Tash.

15
00:02:27,898 --> 00:02:30,901
Eat pizza three days in a row?
I think not.

16
00:02:30,901 --> 00:02:33,320
That's really good.

17
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:35,739
The proportions are perfect...

18
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:38,909
...but do you draw
what you really see?

19
00:02:38,909 --> 00:02:42,913
The simplest is the hardest.
Seeing what's in front of you.

20
00:02:55,968 --> 00:02:57,928
What's on for tonight?

21
00:02:57,928 --> 00:03:01,932
I am so grounded. I got busted
sneaking back inside last night.

22
00:03:02,641 --> 00:03:06,645
-Damn, how'd you manage that?
-My dad set the motion detector.

23
00:03:06,770 --> 00:03:10,232
Our parents are getting
paranoid in their old age.

24
00:03:10,232 --> 00:03:14,236
Mine still trust me.

25
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:19,616
It's beautiful.

26
00:03:19,658 --> 00:03:21,952
Not a bad couple of decades.

27
00:03:21,952 --> 00:03:24,830
Better than the first two
without you.

28
00:03:24,830 --> 00:03:28,834
To 20 years of you and me.

29
00:03:31,670 --> 00:03:35,674
And to our children, safe at home.

30
00:03:42,598 --> 00:03:44,391
Hey, cool, you lost them!

31
00:03:44,391 --> 00:03:47,519
Macho Mustang boys, to boot!

32
00:03:47,519 --> 00:03:51,523
-We struck a blow for sisterhood!
-The only "blow" you know.

33
00:03:51,565 --> 00:03:53,859
Diss.

34
00:03:53,859 --> 00:03:56,570
-Any raves?
-Full Moon Underground.

35
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:59,573
San Bernardino.
Probably Saturday.

36
00:03:59,573 --> 00:04:02,034
I'll tell Mom I'm staying with you.

37
00:04:02,034 --> 00:04:05,454
I can't believe you
still work that scam.

38
00:04:05,454 --> 00:04:09,458
What can I say?
My 'rents are clueless.

39
00:04:10,584 --> 00:04:13,295
I'll bring glowsticks if you buy gas.

40
00:04:13,295 --> 00:04:17,049
-That's such a good idea!
-Nice try, Beams.

41
00:04:17,049 --> 00:04:19,593
Rest, it'll be one hell of a weekend.

42
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:23,555
-Bye, Tasha.
-Don't let the bedbugs bite!

43
00:04:28,018 --> 00:04:32,022
Hasta!

44
00:04:47,037 --> 00:04:51,041
Now they call the cops on me.

45
00:04:58,757 --> 00:05:02,761
Hello!

46
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:08,475
Hello!

47
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:11,061
I'm sorry I'm late.

48
00:05:11,061 --> 00:05:14,898
Ruby Baker?

49
00:05:14,898 --> 00:05:18,902
Yeah, I'm Ruby.

50
00:05:19,486 --> 00:05:23,407
Whatever they said, I'm not missing.
I just went out.

51
00:05:24,992 --> 00:05:27,703
Your parents were in a car accident.

52
00:05:27,703 --> 00:05:30,539
Are they okay?

53
00:05:30,539 --> 00:05:34,501
-Ruby, why don't you have a seat, hon?
-Are they okay?

54
00:05:34,501 --> 00:05:38,088
My partner will help you have a seat.
Ruby.

55
00:05:38,088 --> 00:05:40,090
-I can sit down myself.
-I know.

56
00:05:40,090 --> 00:05:41,383
Are they okay?

57
00:05:41,383 --> 00:05:44,511
-Relax.
-We're here to help you.

58
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:45,971
You'll be okay.

59
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:49,975
Relax. Ruby?

60
00:05:52,853 --> 00:05:54,521
Ruby.

61
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:55,814
You'll be okay.

62
00:05:55,814 --> 00:05:59,818
-Get her pulse.
-Can you hear me, Ruby?

63
00:06:03,697 --> 00:06:05,699
"They are as asleep.

64
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:09,119
In the morning, they're like grass
which groweth up.

65
00:06:09,119 --> 00:06:12,414
In the morning, it flourisheth
and groweth up.

66
00:06:12,414 --> 00:06:16,168
In the evening, it is cut down
and withereth...

67
00:06:16,168 --> 00:06:20,172
...for we're consumed by thine anger
and by thy wrath we're troubled.

68
00:06:21,423 --> 00:06:25,427
Thou has set our iniquities
before thee, our secret sins...

69
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:28,055
...in the light of thy countenance.

70
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:31,934
For all our days are
passed away in thy wrath.

71
00:06:31,934 --> 00:06:34,937
We spend our years as
a tale that is told...

72
00:06:34,937 --> 00:06:37,898
...so teach us to number our days...

73
00:06:37,898 --> 00:06:41,902
...that we may apply
our hearts unto wisdom."

74
00:06:41,902 --> 00:06:45,864
I think Rhett Baker wants to
say something. Rhett?

75
00:07:03,090 --> 00:07:07,094
I just--

76
00:07:07,928 --> 00:07:11,890
I just wanna say....

77
00:07:19,523 --> 00:07:21,108
I just....

78
00:07:21,108 --> 00:07:25,112
It's okay.

79
00:07:29,074 --> 00:07:33,078
I didn't work with Dave and Grace
or see them every day...

80
00:07:33,245 --> 00:07:35,956
...but I knew them for 10 years...

81
00:07:35,956 --> 00:07:39,960
...and I'm sure if they
could hear this....

82
00:07:41,211 --> 00:07:43,130
Well, Grace...

83
00:07:43,130 --> 00:07:47,134
...would do her dismissive
little giggle.

84
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:49,219
You know the one.

85
00:07:49,219 --> 00:07:53,223
And Dave would mutter
an "expletive deleted."

86
00:07:57,603 --> 00:08:00,689
They'd hate to be remembered
as anything but...

87
00:08:00,689 --> 00:08:04,151
...ordinary.

88
00:08:04,151 --> 00:08:07,696
Which is exactly what they were:

89
00:08:07,696 --> 00:08:11,700
Anything but ordinary.

90
00:08:12,034 --> 00:08:14,828
But they will live on...

91
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:18,832
...through their children
and in all our hearts.

92
00:08:24,296 --> 00:08:27,049
Ruby?

93
00:08:27,049 --> 00:08:29,718
Do you remember me?

94
00:08:29,718 --> 00:08:32,638
I'm Uncle Jack,
your mom's brother.

95
00:08:32,638 --> 00:08:36,642
I'll go wait by the car, okay?

96
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:41,647
If there's anything that you need...

97
00:08:41,647 --> 00:08:43,857
...anything I can do...

98
00:08:43,857 --> 00:08:47,861
...I don't mean in the next few weeks
or months, I mean anytime.

99
00:08:49,738 --> 00:08:53,742
How come I haven't seen you
in, like, 10 years?

100
00:08:54,034 --> 00:08:57,037
Have you even met my brother Rhett?

101
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:59,331
Well, of course I have.

102
00:08:59,331 --> 00:09:02,042
I haven't seen either of you in years.

103
00:09:02,042 --> 00:09:05,963
First of all, I live pretty far away.
Chicago.

104
00:09:06,088 --> 00:09:08,882
Then how will you help us?

105
00:09:08,882 --> 00:09:12,803
I don't know.
There's the phone, e-mail.

106
00:09:12,803 --> 00:09:16,807
-You and my mom never wrote.
-That's true.

107
00:09:17,057 --> 00:09:20,352
As siblings get older,
they go separate ways.

108
00:09:20,352 --> 00:09:24,231
-You and Rhett are close now--
-We're not.

109
00:09:24,231 --> 00:09:27,901
We have nothing in common.

110
00:09:27,901 --> 00:09:31,822
Used to feel that way about your mom.
It's not true.

111
00:09:31,989 --> 00:09:35,993
I used to think I'd take a month off
and come out here...

112
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:40,664
...and get to know you,
your brother and Grace again.

113
00:09:41,832 --> 00:09:45,836
Nice to see you.
Sorry things didn't work out.

114
00:09:53,677 --> 00:09:57,681
-I'll call you later, okay?
-Okay.

115
00:10:17,993 --> 00:10:21,705
Ruby? Hi.

116
00:10:21,705 --> 00:10:25,292
-I'm Alvin Begleiter.
-Hi.

117
00:10:25,292 --> 00:10:28,128
I'm so sorry.

118
00:10:28,128 --> 00:10:32,132
I'm your--
I was your parents' estate lawyer.

119
00:10:33,467 --> 00:10:35,886
I planned their wills...

120
00:10:35,886 --> 00:10:39,890
...what they wanted to do
with their money and--

121
00:10:41,642 --> 00:10:45,646
The most important issue right now
is who'll take care of you.

122
00:10:46,939 --> 00:10:48,357
You and Rhett.

123
00:10:48,357 --> 00:10:51,735
I'm assuming you know the Glasses?

124
00:10:51,735 --> 00:10:54,780
I've known them my whole life.

125
00:10:54,780 --> 00:10:57,282
Good. I know that your parents...

126
00:10:57,282 --> 00:11:01,286
...chose them after a great deal
of consideration.

127
00:11:01,286 --> 00:11:03,455
And there's something else.

128
00:11:03,455 --> 00:11:07,084
Your parents were extremely thrifty...

129
00:11:07,084 --> 00:11:11,088
...and with your mom's share,
your dad's life insurance...

130
00:11:13,799 --> 00:11:17,803
...there's enough for you
and Rhett for the rest of your lives.

131
00:11:19,054 --> 00:11:23,058
Obviously you don't know Rhett.

132
00:11:23,767 --> 00:11:27,271
That's good.
I'll give you one of my cards.

133
00:11:27,271 --> 00:11:29,815
I don't expect trouble.

134
00:11:29,815 --> 00:11:33,819
But if you have any concerns,
any problems....

135
00:11:34,903 --> 00:11:38,365
I'm an estate lawyer
and also a trust lawyer.

136
00:11:38,365 --> 00:11:42,369
I want to be someone you can trust.

137
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:51,128
-You call me, okay?
-Okay.

138
00:11:51,128 --> 00:11:55,132
Mr. Glass.

139
00:11:57,134 --> 00:12:01,138
-Ruby.
-Thank you.

140
00:12:01,305 --> 00:12:05,309
My mom and dad would've
loved that speech.

141
00:12:06,310 --> 00:12:10,314
-They would've loved it.
-Come here.

142
00:12:12,149 --> 00:12:16,153
That's good.
We're gonna get through this.

143
00:12:17,029 --> 00:12:20,991
We'll get through it together, okay?

144
00:12:24,953 --> 00:12:27,247
Oh, Ruby.

145
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:31,251
You're in good hands.

146
00:12:58,570 --> 00:13:00,781
Hey!

147
00:13:00,781 --> 00:13:04,785
-You guys ready for Malibu?
-It'll be a change, we won't lie.

148
00:13:05,786 --> 00:13:07,579
It's not the worst place.

149
00:13:07,579 --> 00:13:11,583
-Is this your car?
-My company's, on loan for today.

150
00:14:00,591 --> 00:14:04,595
Sweet!

151
00:14:04,928 --> 00:14:08,932
This place is huge!

152
00:14:11,268 --> 00:14:14,021
Hey, Rubes, check out this view.

153
00:14:14,021 --> 00:14:18,025
Yeah, it's pretty amazing.

154
00:14:21,987 --> 00:14:25,991
-Cool, a meteorite!
-It's art, Rhett.

155
00:14:26,950 --> 00:14:30,454
Give them the tour.
Stall them, I'll order dinner.

156
00:14:30,454 --> 00:14:34,458
Let's get the lay of the land.

157
00:14:38,128 --> 00:14:41,340
Master suite.

158
00:14:41,340 --> 00:14:45,052
Home gym.

159
00:14:45,052 --> 00:14:48,055
-Home theater.
-Sweet.

160
00:14:48,055 --> 00:14:52,059
-You never have to leave home.
-If only.

161
00:14:52,142 --> 00:14:54,353
Vicki comes in most days.

162
00:14:54,353 --> 00:14:56,271
-Hola, niños.
-Hola.

163
00:14:56,271 --> 00:15:00,150
Hello!

164
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:03,946
This is your room.

165
00:15:03,946 --> 00:15:07,491
It's temporary quarters, of course.

166
00:15:07,491 --> 00:15:11,495
Unpack, get settled,
and I'll meet you in the kitchen.

167
00:15:15,499 --> 00:15:19,503
We're sharing a room?

168
00:15:22,381 --> 00:15:26,343
Glance at me when I'm changing
and you're busted.

169
00:15:27,052 --> 00:15:31,056
We have a little calamari,
a little risotto with mushrooms...

170
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:37,104
...and green salad with
some Swiss chard.

171
00:15:43,235 --> 00:15:47,239
-Do you have any Garfield?
-What is that?

172
00:15:47,239 --> 00:15:51,243
-It's crap in a can.
-If it's crap, how come you eat it?

173
00:15:51,535 --> 00:15:55,539
-Come on, kids. Try the calamari.
-Isn't that squid?

174
00:16:02,087 --> 00:16:06,091
-Honey, tonight....
-I'll call Domino's.

175
00:16:06,550 --> 00:16:10,554
Thank you.

176
00:16:24,234 --> 00:16:27,738
Can you turn and face the wall?

177
00:16:27,738 --> 00:16:29,698
Who are you, the Blair Witch?

178
00:16:29,698 --> 00:16:33,577
I'm worse. Just face the wall.

179
00:16:33,577 --> 00:16:37,581
Turn that stupid thing off!

180
00:17:27,756 --> 00:17:30,801
There's public school,
then there's public school.

181
00:17:30,801 --> 00:17:34,638
Trust me, there won't be any
Bloods or Crips.

182
00:17:34,638 --> 00:17:37,349
I'm not scared of getting gunned down.

183
00:17:37,349 --> 00:17:41,228
-You're a great kid--
-It's not about being great.

184
00:17:41,228 --> 00:17:44,189
-It's about being....
-New?

185
00:17:44,189 --> 00:17:47,067
Middle-of-the-year new.

186
00:17:47,067 --> 00:17:51,071
There's a saying we teach
the Pain Ward patients.

187
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:54,658
"This too shall pass."

188
00:17:54,658 --> 00:17:58,662
This too shall pass.
This too shall pass.

189
00:18:01,540 --> 00:18:02,791
Hi.

190
00:18:02,791 --> 00:18:06,795
Why don't you take
a seat in the back?

191
00:18:15,846 --> 00:18:18,432
We have a new addition.

192
00:18:18,432 --> 00:18:22,436
Would you introduce yourself,
Miss Baker?

193
00:18:23,562 --> 00:18:27,566
You just did.

194
00:18:31,570 --> 00:18:34,865
Hi.

195
00:18:34,865 --> 00:18:38,869
I'm Ruby Baker.

196
00:18:39,453 --> 00:18:43,457
I used to go to Shady Lane.
That's in the Valley.

197
00:18:44,708 --> 00:18:48,712
Not my choice,
just an accident of birth.

198
00:18:49,463 --> 00:18:52,466
How come you moved here?

199
00:18:52,466 --> 00:18:56,428
It was another accident.

200
00:18:57,596 --> 00:19:01,600
Let's make Ruby feel welcome.

201
00:19:15,739 --> 00:19:19,743
Thanks for the lift.

202
00:19:20,327 --> 00:19:24,331
Sweet!

203
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,627
I can't believe it!

204
00:19:28,627 --> 00:19:31,630
Like one of those isn't noisy enough?

205
00:19:31,630 --> 00:19:35,634
No, Rubes. You can't play
"Pokémon Snap" on PlayStation.

206
00:19:35,968 --> 00:19:39,805
You can play "Ape Escape,"
but not on N-64.

207
00:19:39,805 --> 00:19:43,809
Mom and Dad would freak out.

208
00:19:44,351 --> 00:19:48,355
Don't talk about them.

209
00:20:08,667 --> 00:20:11,962
I haven't seen one girl
with blue-black hair.

210
00:20:11,962 --> 00:20:15,966
The guys surf and swim all day.
That sun-worshiping culture.

211
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:18,385
That sounds hot.

212
00:20:18,385 --> 00:20:22,389
I checked my pager all day.
I figured you'd call and you didn't.

213
00:20:23,390 --> 00:20:27,311
Cell phones are banned at school.
The kids don't care.

214
00:20:27,853 --> 00:20:30,814
They can't see they
lost their liberties.

215
00:20:30,814 --> 00:20:34,693
They have so much sunstroke,
they're wasted.

216
00:20:34,693 --> 00:20:38,697
Ruby?

217
00:20:40,324 --> 00:20:43,994
I got us an assortment
of different things.

218
00:20:43,994 --> 00:20:47,998
Some cold pastas, some salads.

219
00:20:52,419 --> 00:20:56,340
Ruby, I think that you'd be
well-served by a better attitude.

220
00:21:02,888 --> 00:21:06,892
It's okay. I don't mind take-out.
You're busy.

221
00:21:06,892 --> 00:21:08,727
It's not from Wendy's.

222
00:21:08,727 --> 00:21:12,731
I meant your attitude
toward your new school.

223
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:18,904
-My attitude?
-I overheard your conversation.

224
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:21,907
You were listening in?

225
00:21:21,907 --> 00:21:25,911
No, I was trying to get a line out,
but that's beside the point.

226
00:21:26,912 --> 00:21:30,499
The point is, you need those
kids to like you.

227
00:21:30,499 --> 00:21:33,627
Otherwise, you'll isolate,
sabotage yourself.

228
00:21:33,627 --> 00:21:37,631
-You'll have a miserable time.
-Okay, I get it.

229
00:21:43,512 --> 00:21:47,516
I learned something.

230
00:21:53,522 --> 00:21:55,524
Ruby?

231
00:21:55,524 --> 00:21:57,776
Ruby.

232
00:21:57,776 --> 00:22:01,780
-Wake up.
-I'm awake.

233
00:22:02,781 --> 00:22:06,785
-Wake up.
-Mommy?

234
00:22:08,495 --> 00:22:12,499
Mommy?

235
00:23:20,192 --> 00:23:23,445
You scared the crap out of me.

236
00:23:23,445 --> 00:23:27,449
I heard noises. I thought
it was a burglar or coyote.

237
00:23:27,574 --> 00:23:31,203
I'm not used to kids here.

238
00:23:31,203 --> 00:23:35,207
Come here.

239
00:23:39,044 --> 00:23:43,048
Thank you.

240
00:23:51,807 --> 00:23:54,601
You must be freezing.

241
00:23:54,601 --> 00:23:58,605
No more 3 a.m. swims. With all
the glass, you hear everything.

242
00:23:59,523 --> 00:24:02,943
I'll set the alarm at night.

243
00:24:02,943 --> 00:24:06,947
Are you coming?

244
00:24:13,203 --> 00:24:15,956
Drunk driving among teens has...

245
00:24:15,956 --> 00:24:19,251
...steadily decreased,
but we can do better.

246
00:24:19,251 --> 00:24:22,004
As these images starkly attest...

247
00:24:22,004 --> 00:24:26,008
...alcohol remains the No. 1
problem among teens.

248
00:24:26,842 --> 00:24:30,846
This year, 20 percent
of teenage drivers....

249
00:24:55,621 --> 00:24:59,625
How was your first day
of Driver's Ed?

250
00:24:59,875 --> 00:25:03,879
-Fine, I guess.
-They still show gruesome movies?

251
00:25:04,713 --> 00:25:06,715
Those were the Dark Ages.

252
00:25:06,715 --> 00:25:10,302
They have better ways
of teaching kids today.

253
00:25:10,302 --> 00:25:14,306
May I be excused?

254
00:25:22,856 --> 00:25:26,777
Stupid, kid-proof piece of crap.

255
00:25:28,612 --> 00:25:32,616
Ruby?

256
00:25:32,658 --> 00:25:36,662
Was it awful?
I mean, the driving class?

257
00:25:37,329 --> 00:25:41,333
-I can just imagine.
-No, it's....

258
00:25:44,253 --> 00:25:48,257
I have my period.

259
00:25:49,049 --> 00:25:53,053
Come with me.

260
00:26:04,189 --> 00:26:08,193
Thank you.

261
00:26:15,617 --> 00:26:18,787
Four doctors recommend....

262
00:26:18,787 --> 00:26:22,791
This cramp, too, shall pass.

263
00:26:25,252 --> 00:26:29,214
I'll turn it off
when I get to a save point.

264
00:26:30,382 --> 00:26:34,386
It's cool. I don't care.

265
00:26:35,262 --> 00:26:39,224
It's kind of relaxing.

266
00:27:02,289 --> 00:27:05,709
Erin, get out of there!

267
00:27:05,709 --> 00:27:09,129
What were you doing in there?
Tell me the truth!

268
00:27:09,129 --> 00:27:11,423
-What are you implying?
-Tell me!

269
00:27:11,423 --> 00:27:14,426
No, I won't answer you!
Good night!

270
00:27:14,426 --> 00:27:18,430
-What the hell are you doing?
-Getting ready for bed.

271
00:27:18,722 --> 00:27:22,726
-Watch your language.
-Don't play games with me.

272
00:27:22,851 --> 00:27:25,312
You know what I'm talking about.

273
00:27:25,312 --> 00:27:29,316
I'm too tired to guess.
I'm sick of your accusations.

274
00:27:29,483 --> 00:27:32,444
Is that what you call it now?

275
00:27:32,444 --> 00:27:34,655
-How many--
